column6:
In the premiere episode of Rewriting the Narrative, host Ben Tillson is joined by Dr. Danielle Kovach, a seasoned special education teacher and adjunct professor, and Glenna Wright-Gallo, vice president of policy at Everway and former U.S. assistant secretary for special education and rehabilitation services. Together, they share their journeys into special education, reflect on the evolving challenges of the profession, and explore critical issues like funding, staffing shortages, and the growing role of technology‚Äîincluding AI‚Äîin supporting students. They also emphasize the power of community, collaboration, and policy in shaping a sustainable, more inclusive future for educators and learners alike.

https://exceptionalchildren.podbean.com/e/building-a-better-future-funding-tech-and-the-special-education-workforce

Together, they share their journeys into special education, reflect on the evolving challenges of the profession, and explore critical issues like funding, staffing shortages, and the growing role of technology‚Äîincluding AI‚Äîin supporting students. They also emphasize the power of community, collaboration, and policy in shaping a sustainable, more inclusive future for educators and learners alike.

column6:
We are excited to welcome you to Baltimore for #CEC2025! Explore the Expo Hall, where you can meet exhibitors ready to provide resources, tools, and solutions to address any needs or challenges you may face. Be sure to visit the CEC-ISET Technology Playground, where innovative assistive and instructional technology comes to life. This hands-on, immersive space is an excellent opportunity to connect with vendors, educators, and students, all demonstrating tools designed to support your students. You can earn up to one Continuing Education Unit (CEU) as you explore! The Tech Playground will be open to all attendees from  March 12 through March 14.

https://cecconvention.org/convention-news/cec2025-explore-expo-hall-technology-playground-and-wellness-pavilion
